{"title_page": "How I'm Feeling Now", "text_new": "{{distinguish|How I'm Feeling}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = How I'm Feeling Now\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Charli XCX]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          =\n| released     = {{start date|2020|05|15|df=y}}\n| recorded     = 6 April 2020 \u2013 present\n| studio       =\n| genre        =\n| length       = \n| label        =\n*[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n*[[Asylum Records|Asylum]]\n| producer     =\n* Charli XCX\n* [[A. G. Cook]]\n* [[BJ Burton]]\n* [[100 Gecs|Dylan Brady]]\n| prev_title   = [[Charli (album)|Charli]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = How I'm Feeling Now\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Forever (Charli XCX song)|Forever]]\n | single1date = 9 April 2020\n | single2     = Claws<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249834442849312768 |title=this is coming next but i still don't have the official title.. the demo was called \"claws\". it could also be called \"i like\" / \"i like everything about you\" troye commented that \"clementines\" is a good title coz of the lyrics in the 2nd verse (tweeted below). what do u think? |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Charli XCX\">{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249864906666463232 |title=ok i\u2019m calling it \"claws\" \ud83e\udd0d |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n | single2date = 23 April 2020<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx|number= 1253300015692427272|title=CLAWS DROPS 2DAY AT 5PM BST/9AM PST | ARTWORK BY \n@TMTHYLUKE | 2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS COMING LATER 2DAY | THANK U FOR CHOOSING THIS SONG ANGELS|date=23 April 2020|access date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n'''''How I'm Feeling Now''''' is the working title of the upcoming fourth studio album by English singer and songwriter [[Charli XCX]], scheduled for release on 15 May 2020. The album is a \"do-it-yourself\" collaborative process with Charli XCX involving her fans in the recording process. The recording and title was inspired by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Background==\nOn 13 September 2019, Charli XCX released her third studio album ''[[Charli (album)|Charli]]''. To celebrate the one month anniversary of ''Charli'', Charli XCX announced that the album wouldn't receive a deluxe edition and that she already began work on a new project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/charli-xcx-reveals-shes-started-working-on-her-next-album|title=Charli XCX reveals she\u2019s started working on her next album|date=14 October 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|author=Cerys Kenneally}}</ref> Soon after, on 24 November 2019, Charli XCX announced on [[Twitter]] that she was planning to record two new albums in 2020, with plans to release both by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/charli-xcx-reveals-she-wants-to-release-two-albums-in-2020|title=Charli XCX reveals she wants to release two albums in 2020|date=25 November 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|author=Cerys Kenneally|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]}}</ref> On 18 March 2020, in response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]], Charli XCX began a [[Isolation (health care)#Self-isolation|self-isolating]] livestream series featuring artists such as [[Diplo]], [[Clairo]] and [[Rita Ora]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9337373/charli-xcx-livestream-series|title=Charli XCX Launches 'Self-Isolating' Livestream Series With Rita Ora, Diplo, Clairo and More Pals|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=18 March 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|author=Gil Kaufman}}</ref>\n\n{{external media\n| float = right\n| width  = 270px\n| video1 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JDlubOmyZOs \"How I'm Feeling Now\" Announcement Zoom], via [[YouTube]]}}\nOn 6 April 2020, Charli XCX announced through a public [[Zoom Video Communications|Zoom]] call with fans that she'd be working on a new album in self-isolation, with the tentative title ''How I'm Feeling Now''.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9352433/charli-xcx-how-im-feeling-now-self-isolation-album|title=Charli XCX Will Express 'How I'm Feeling Now' in Upcoming Self-Isolated Album|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|website=Billboard|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> In the call, Charli XCX stated \"The nature of this album is going to be very indicative of the times just because I\u2019m only going to be able to use the tools I have at my fingertips to create all music, artwork, videos everything.\"<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> The entire project will be collaborative with her fans, using future Zoom calls to share demos and text conversations with producers and ask fan input on single releases, song ideas, and artwork.<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/charli-xcx-how-im-feeling-now-979219/|title=Charli XCX Announces \u2018DIY\u2019 Quarantine Album 'How I'm Feeling Now'|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> She also said in the stream that [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]] are among the people she is working with.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JDlubOmyZOs|title=Charli XCX - \"How I'm Feeling Now\" Announcement Zoom|website=YouTube|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> During the Zoom announcement, Charli XCX set a release date of 15 May 2020.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/><ref name=\"RS\"/> On 7 April 2020, Charli shared snippets of a song called \"Forever\" on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-clip-album-2642649|title=Listen to a clip of Charli XCX\u2019s new song \u2018Forever\u2019 from upcoming quarantine album|date=7 April 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[NME]]|author=Tom Skinner}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2020, Charli XCX announced that \"Forever\" would be released at 11:30 PM [[Pacific Standard Time|PST]] and premiere on the [[BBC Radio 1]] with [[Annie Mac]] [[Annie Mac (radio show)|podcast]]. \"Forever\"'s official artwork was created by American artist [[Seth Bogart (artist)|Seth Bogart]]. Two additional artworks were also released for \"Forever\", by French artist Regards Coupables and American singer-songwriter [[Caroline Polachek]], respectively.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248287541306036225 |title=\ud83d\udc93 FOREVER DROPS AT 7.30PM BST/11:30AM PST PREMIERING AS HOTTEST RECORD ON @ANNIEMAC ON @BBCR1!!!!! ARTWORK BY @SETHBOGARTOK!!!  2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS TO COME LATER IN THE DAY \ud83d\udc93 THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME CREATE THE FIRST SONG FROM \"HOW I\u2019M FEELING NOW\" \ud83d\udc93 |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248043315951370240 |title=fyi i am making multiple official artworks for every song I release before the album, maybe even multiple album covers too. the \"forever\" artwork will be based of the photo we selected together and will be visually interpreted by @SethBogartOK @carolineplz and @regardscoupable \ud83d\udc93 |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> The official music video for \"Forever\", featuring clips sent in from fans, was released on 17 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/charli-xcx-forever-video-986029/|title=Charli XCX\u2019s \u2018Forever\u2019 Video Is a Shining Document of Quarantine Life|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|publisher=Rolling Stone|date=17 April 2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April 2020 she announced that she had chosen the next single, to be titled either \"Claws\" or \"I Like\".<ref name=\"i'm gonna release i like\">{{cite tweet|user=charli_xcx|number=1249066384278970368|title=i'm gonna release \"i like/claws\" next (haven't decided on a title yet) thanks for helping me decide Beating heart which photo should i base the artwork of off? 1, 2, 3 or 4???|date=11 April 2020|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> On 14 April 2020 she announced that she had settled on \"Claws\" as the song title.<ref name=\"Charli XCX\">{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249864906666463232 |title=ok i\u2019m calling it \"claws\" \ud83e\udd0d |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref> The three official artworks for \"Claws\" were created by Canadian artist [[Sara Cwynar]], American graphic designer Timothy Luke and South Korean artist Hang Seung Hee.\n\n==Confirmed tracks==\n*\"[[Forever (Charli XCX song)|Forever]]\" (4:03)\n*\"Claws\"<ref name=\"i'm gonna release i like\"/> (2:29)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.howimfeelingnow.co.uk/ Official ''How <nowiki>I'm</nowiki> Feeling Now'' website]\n\n{{Charli XCX}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Charli XCX albums]]\n[[Category:Responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded in a home studio]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by A. G. Cook]]\n[[Category:Upcoming albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|How I'm Feeling}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = How I'm Feeling Now\n| type         = studio\n| artist       = [[Charli XCX]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          =\n| released     = {{start date|2020|05|15|df=y}}\n| recorded     = 6 April 2020 \u2013 present\n| studio       =\n| genre        =\n| length       = \n| label        =\n*[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n*[[Asylum Records]]\n| producer     =\n* Charli XCX\n* [[A. G. Cook]]\n* [[BJ Burton]]\n* [[100 Gecs|Dylan Brady]]\n| prev_title   = [[Charli (album)|Charli]]\n| prev_year    = 2019\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = How I'm Feeling Now\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Forever (Charli XCX song)|Forever]]\n | single1date = 9 April 2020\n | single2     = Claws<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249834442849312768 |title=this is coming next but i still don't have the official title.. the demo was called \"claws\". it could also be called \"i like\" / \"i like everything about you\" troye commented that \"clementines\" is a good title coz of the lyrics in the 2nd verse (tweeted below). what do u think? |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Charli XCX\">{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249864906666463232 |title=ok i\u2019m calling it \"claws\" \ud83e\udd0d |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n | single2date = 23 April 2020<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx|number= 1253300015692427272|title=CLAWS DROPS 2DAY AT 5PM BST/9AM PST | ARTWORK BY \n@TMTHYLUKE | 2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS COMING LATER 2DAY | THANK U FOR CHOOSING THIS SONG ANGELS|date=23 April 2020|access date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n'''''How I'm Feeling Now''''' is the working title of the upcoming fourth studio album by English singer and songwriter [[Charli XCX]], scheduled for release on 15 May 2020. The album is a \"do-it-yourself\" collaborative process with Charli XCX involving her fans in the recording process. The recording and title was inspired by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Background==\nOn 13 September 2019, Charli XCX released her third studio album ''[[Charli (album)|Charli]]''. To celebrate the one month anniversary of ''Charli'', Charli XCX announced that the album wouldn't receive a deluxe edition and that she already began work on a new project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/charli-xcx-reveals-shes-started-working-on-her-next-album|title=Charli XCX reveals she\u2019s started working on her next album|date=14 October 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]|author=Cerys Kenneally}}</ref> Soon after, on 24 November 2019, Charli XCX announced on [[Twitter]] that she was planning to record two new albums in 2020, with plans to release both by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelineofbestfit.com/news/latest-news/charli-xcx-reveals-she-wants-to-release-two-albums-in-2020|title=Charli XCX reveals she wants to release two albums in 2020|date=25 November 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|author=Cerys Kenneally|website=[[The Line of Best Fit]]}}</ref> On 18 March 2020, in response to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]], Charli XCX began a [[Isolation (health care)#Self-isolation|self-isolating]] livestream series featuring artists such as [[Diplo]], [[Clairo]] and [[Rita Ora]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9337373/charli-xcx-livestream-series|title=Charli XCX Launches 'Self-Isolating' Livestream Series With Rita Ora, Diplo, Clairo and More Pals|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=18 March 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|author=Gil Kaufman}}</ref>\n\n{{external media\n| float = right\n| width  = 270px\n| video1 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JDlubOmyZOs \"How I'm Feeling Now\" Announcement Zoom], via [[YouTube]]}}\nOn 6 April 2020, Charli XCX announced through a public [[Zoom Video Communications|Zoom]] call with fans that she'd be working on a new album in self-isolation, with the tentative title ''How I'm Feeling Now''.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9352433/charli-xcx-how-im-feeling-now-self-isolation-album|title=Charli XCX Will Express 'How I'm Feeling Now' in Upcoming Self-Isolated Album|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|website=Billboard|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> In the call, Charli XCX stated \"The nature of this album is going to be very indicative of the times just because I\u2019m only going to be able to use the tools I have at my fingertips to create all music, artwork, videos everything.\"<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> The entire project will be collaborative with her fans, using future Zoom calls to share demos and text conversations with producers and ask fan input on single releases, song ideas, and artwork.<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/charli-xcx-how-im-feeling-now-979219/|title=Charli XCX Announces \u2018DIY\u2019 Quarantine Album 'How I'm Feeling Now'|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> She also said in the stream that [[A. G. Cook]] and [[BJ Burton]] are among the people she is working with.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JDlubOmyZOs|title=Charli XCX - \"How I'm Feeling Now\" Announcement Zoom|website=YouTube|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref> During the Zoom announcement, Charli XCX set a release date of 15 May 2020.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/><ref name=\"RS\"/> On 7 April 2020, Charli shared snippets of a song called \"Forever\" on social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/charli-xcx-new-song-forever-clip-album-2642649|title=Listen to a clip of Charli XCX\u2019s new song \u2018Forever\u2019 from upcoming quarantine album|date=7 April 2020|accessdate=8 April 2020|website=[[NME]]|author=Tom Skinner}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April 2020, Charli XCX announced that \"Forever\" would be released at 11:30 PM [[Pacific Standard Time|PST]] and premiere on the [[BBC Radio 1]] with [[Annie Mac]] [[Annie Mac (radio show)|podcast]]. \"Forever\"'s official artwork was created by American artist [[Seth Bogart (artist)|Seth Bogart]]. Two additional artworks were also released for \"Forever\", by French artist Regards Coupables and American singer-songwriter [[Caroline Polachek]], respectively.<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248287541306036225 |title=\ud83d\udc93 FOREVER DROPS AT 7.30PM BST/11:30AM PST PREMIERING AS HOTTEST RECORD ON @ANNIEMAC ON @BBCR1!!!!! ARTWORK BY @SETHBOGARTOK!!!  2 MORE OFFICIAL ARTWORKS TO COME LATER IN THE DAY \ud83d\udc93 THANK YOU FOR HELPING ME CREATE THE FIRST SONG FROM \"HOW I\u2019M FEELING NOW\" \ud83d\udc93 |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet |user=charli_xcx |number=1248043315951370240 |title=fyi i am making multiple official artworks for every song I release before the album, maybe even multiple album covers too. the \"forever\" artwork will be based of the photo we selected together and will be visually interpreted by @SethBogartOK @carolineplz and @regardscoupable \ud83d\udc93 |date=8 April 2020 |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> The official music video for \"Forever\", featuring clips sent in from fans, was released on 17 April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/charli-xcx-forever-video-986029/|title=Charli XCX\u2019s \u2018Forever\u2019 Video Is a Shining Document of Quarantine Life|last=Shaffer|first=Claire|publisher=Rolling Stone|date=17 April 2020|accessdate=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April 2020 she announced that she had chosen the next single, to be titled either \"Claws\" or \"I Like\".<ref name=\"i'm gonna release i like\">{{cite tweet|user=charli_xcx|number=1249066384278970368|title=i'm gonna release \"i like/claws\" next (haven't decided on a title yet) thanks for helping me decide Beating heart which photo should i base the artwork of off? 1, 2, 3 or 4???|date=11 April 2020|accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> On 14 April 2020 she announced that she had settled on \"Claws\" as the song title.<ref name=\"Charli XCX\">{{Cite tweet |author=Charli XCX |user=charli_xcx |number=1249864906666463232 |title=ok i\u2019m calling it \"claws\" \ud83e\udd0d |date=14 April 2020 |access date=14 April 2020}}</ref> The three official artworks for \"Claws\" were created by Canadian artist [[Sara Cwynar]], American graphic designer Timothy Luke and South Korean artist Hang Seung Hee.\n\n==Confirmed tracks==\n*\"[[Forever (Charli XCX song)|Forever]]\" (4:03)\n*\"Claws\"<ref name=\"i'm gonna release i like\"/> (2:29)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.howimfeelingnow.co.uk/ Official ''How <nowiki>I'm</nowiki> Feeling Now'' website]\n\n{{Charli XCX}}\n\n[[Category:2020 albums]]\n[[Category:Charli XCX albums]]\n[[Category:Responses to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded in a home studio]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by A. G. Cook]]\n[[Category:Upcoming albums]]\n", "name_user": "Gagaluv1", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/How_I%27m_Feeling_Now"}
