 U.S. Senate from the Great State of Alabama. Tommy was a terrific head football coach at Auburn University. He is a REAL LEADER who will never let MAGA/KAG, or our Country, down! Tommy will protect your Second Amendment....|date=March 10, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|user=realDonaldTrump|number=1237557412048986120|title=....(which is under siege), is strong on Crime and the Border, and truly LOVES our Military and our Vets. He will be a great Senator for the people of Alabama. Coach Tommy Tuberville, a winner, has my Complete and Total Endorsement. I love Alabama!|date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n; Individuals\n* Mark Culver, Chairman of the [[Houston County, Alabama|Houston County]] Board of Commissioners<ref name=\"TubervilleEndorsements\"/>\n* John Ferguson, [[Dothan, Alabama|Dothan]] City Commissioner<ref name=\"TubervilleEndorsements\"/>\n* Randall Lewis, Mayor of [[Rockford, Alabama|Rockford]]<ref name=\"TubervilleEndorsements\">{{Cite web |url=https://tommyforsenate.com/coach-tuberville-announces-support/ |title=Coach Tuberville Announces Support |date=July 30, 2019 |website=Tommy Tuberville for U.S. Senate}}</ref>\n* [[Sean Spicer]], former White House Press Secretary<ref>{{cite web|last=Burke|first=Holly|url=https://www.al.com/auburnfootball/2019/04/tommy-tuberville-opens-up-about-running-for-us-senate-sean-spicer-and-the-need-for-patriots.html|title=Tommy Tuberville opens up about running for U.S. Senate, Sean Spicer and the need for \u2018patriots\u2019|work=Alabama Media Group|date=March 13, 2019|accessdate=April 8, 2019}}</ref>\n; Organizations\n* [[Alabama Farmers Federation]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.alreporter.com/2019/09/25/alabama-farmers-federation-endorses-trump-tuberville-and-cavanaugh/|title=Alabama Farmers Federation endorses Trump, Tuberville and Cavanaugh|work=Alabama Political Reporter|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=September 28, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===First round===\n====Polling====\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;te