ons in Alabama|2020]]\n[[Category:2020 United States Senate elections|Alabama]]\n[[Category:2020 Alabama elections|United States Senate]]\n", "name_user": "PutItOnAMap", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePolling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_United_States_Senate_election_in_Alabama"}
{"title_page": "Pacritinib", "text_new": "{{Drugbox\n| IUPAC_name = (16''E'')-11-[2-(1-Pyrrolidinyl)ethoxy]-14,19-dioxa-5,7,26-triazatetracyclo[19.3.1.1<sup>2,6</sup>.1<sup>8,12</sup>]heptacosa-1(25),2(26),3,5,8,10,12(27),16,21,23-decaene\n| image = Pacritinib skeletal.svg\n| width = 230\n| alt = \n| caption =\n\n<!-- Clinical data -->\n| tradename = \n| Drugs.com = \n| MedlinePlus = \n| pregnancy_AU = <!-- A / B1 / B2 / B3 / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_US      = <!-- A / B / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_category= \n| legal_AU = <!-- S2, S3, S4, S5, S6, S7, S8, S9 or Unscheduled-->\n| legal_CA = <!-- OTC, Rx-only, Schedule I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII -->\n| legal_UK = <!-- GSL, P, POM, CD, CD Lic, CD POM, CD No Reg POM, CD (Benz) POM, CD (Anab) POM or CD Inv POM -->\n| legal_US = <!-- OTC / Rx-only / Schedule I, II, III, IV, V -->\n| legal_status = Investigational\n| routes_of_administration = Oral\n\n<!-- Pharmacokinetic data -->\n| bioavailability = \n| protein_bound = \n| metabolism = \n| elimination_half-life = \n| excretion =\n\n<!-- Identifiers -->\n| CAS_number = 937272-79-2\n| UNII_Ref = {{fdacite|correct|FDA}}\n| UNII = G22N65IL3O\n| ATCvet = \n| ATC_prefix = None\n| ATC_suffix = \n| PubChem = 46216796\n| DrugBank = \n| KEGG = D11768\n| ChemSpiderID = 28518965 \n| ChEMBL = 2035187\n| synonyms = SB1518\n\n<!-- Chemical data -->\n| C=28 | H=32 | N=4 | O=3\n| molecular_weight  = 472.58 g/mol\n| smiles = c1cc2cc(c1)-c3ccnc(n3)Nc4ccc(c(c4)COC/C=C/COC2)OCCN5CCCC5\n| StdInChI=1S/C28H32N4O3/c1-2-13-32(12-1)14-17-35-27-9-8-25-19-24(27)21-34-16-4-3-15-33-20-22-6-5-7-23(18-22)26-10-11-29-28(30-25)31-26/h3-11,18-19H,1-2,12-17,20-21H2,(H,29,30,31)/b4-3+\n| StdInChIKey = HWXVIOGONBBTBY-ONEGZZNKSA-N\n}}\n'''Pacritinib''' ([[International Nonproprietary Name|INN]]<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://apps.who.int/iris/bitstream/10665/74579/1/24_4_2010_INN104.pdf|journal=WHO Drug Information|volume=24|issue=4|year=2010|title=International Nonproprietary Names for Pharmaceutical Substances (INN) List 104|page=386}}</ref>) is a [[macrocyclic]] [[Janus kinase inhibitor]] that is being developed for the treatment of [[myelofibrosis]]. It mainly inhibits [[Janus kinase 2]] (JAK2) and [[Fms-like tyrosine kinase 3]] (FLT3). The drug was in [[Phase III clinical trial]]s {{as of|2013|lc=y}}.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.pharmazeutische-zeitung.de/index.php?id=46539|title=JAK-Inhibitoren: Neue Wirkstoffe f\u00fcr viele Indikationen|language=German|journal=Pharmazeutische Zeitung|issue=21|year=2013}}</ref> The drug was discovered in Singapore at the labs of S*BIO Pte Ltd. It is a potent JAK2 inhibitor with activity of IC<sub>50</sub> = 23&nbsp;[[nanomolar|nM]] for the JAK2WT variant and 19&nbsp;nM for JAK2V617F with very good selectivity against [[JAK1]] and [[JAK3]] (IC<sub>50</sub> = 1280 and 520 nM, respectively).<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = William AD, Lee AC, Blanchard S, Poulsen A, Teo EL, Nagaraj H, Tan E, Chen D, Williams M, Sun ET, Goh KC, Ong WC, Goh SK, Hart S, Jayaraman R, Pasha MK, Ethirajulu K, Wood JM, Dymock BW | display-authors = 6 | title = Discovery of the macrocycle 11-(2-pyrrolidin-1-yl-ethoxy)-14,19-dioxa-5,7,26-triaza-tetracyclo[19.3.1.1(2,6).1(8,12)]heptacosa-1(25),2(26),3,5,8,10,12(27),16,21,23-decaene (SB1518), a potent Janus kinase 2/fms-like tyrosine kinase-3 (JAK2/FLT3) inhibitor for the treatment of myelofibrosis and lymphoma | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 54 | issue = 13 | pages = 4638\u201358 | date = July 2011 | pmid = 21604762 | doi = 10.1021/jm200326p }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Poulsen A, William A, Blanchard S, Lee A, Nagaraj H, Wang H, Teo E, Tan E, Goh KC, Dymock B | display-authors = 6 | title = Structure-based design of oxygen-linked macrocyclic kinase inhibitors: discovery of SB1518 and SB1578, potent inhibitors of Janus kinase 2 (JAK2) and Fms-like tyrosine kinase-3 (FLT3) | journal = Journal of Computer-Aided Molecular Design | volume = 26 | issue = 4 | pages = 437\u201350 | date = April 2012 | pmid = 22527961 | doi = 10.1007/s10822-012-9572-z | bibcode = 2012JCAMD..26..437P }}</ref> \n\nThe drug was acquired by Cell Therapeutics, Inc. (CTI) and [[Baxter International]] and could effectively address an unmet medical need for patients living with myelofibrosis who face treatment-emergent thrombocytopenia on marketed JAK inhibitors.<ref>{{cite web | title = Baxter licenses cancer drug from CTI in $172m deal | url = http://www.pmlive.com/pharma_news/baxter_licenses_cancer_drug_from_cti_in_$172m_deal_519143 | work = PMLiVE | date = 2013-11-18 }}</ref> When [[Shire Pharmaceuticals]] purchased [[Baxalta]], a spin-off of Baxter Pharmaceuticals, they halted the development of the drug and ended their partnership with CTI.<ref>{{cite web | title = Pacritinib | url = http://www.ctibiopharma.com/pipeline/pacritinib/ | work = CTI BioPharma Corp }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Shire ends pacritinib development deal with CTI post Baxalta merger | url = http://www.in-pharmatechnologist.com/Regulatory-Safety/Shire-ends-pacritinib-development-deal-with-CTI-post-Baxalta-merger | work = in-PharmaTechnologist | publisher = William Reed Business Media Ltd }}</reF>\n\nThe drug was given fast-track status in 2014.<ref>{{cite web | first = Ben | last = Adams | name-list-format = vanc | date = 29 August 2016 | title = Struggling CTI reveals new pacritinib data, misses a primary endpoint | work = Fierce Biotech | url = http://www.fiercebiotech.com/biotech/struggling-cti-reveals-new-pacritinib-data-misses-a-primary-endpoint}}</ref>\nIn 2016, the FDA placed a full clinical hold on pacritinib due to concerns about increased mortality in patients receiving the drug in the \"PERSIST-2\" trial.<ref>{{cite web | title = CTI BioPharma's (CTIC) Pacritinib Placed on Full Clinical Hold; NDA Withdrawn | url = http://www.streetinsider.com/Corporate+News/CTI+BioPharmas+(CTIC)+Pacritinib+Placed+on+Full+Clinical+Hold%3B+NDA+Withdrawn/11297746.html | work = StreetInsider | date = 10 February 2016 }}</ref> The clinical hold was lifted in January 2017.<ref name=\"Newswire2017\">{{cite web|title=CTI BioPharma Announces Removal Of Full Clinical Hold On Pacritinib|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/cti-biopharma-announces-removal-of-full-clinical-hold-on-pacritinib-300386115.html|website=PR Newswire|access-date=18 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Extracellular chemotherapeutic agents}}\n{{Cytokine receptor modulators}}\n\n[[Category:Pyrrolidines]]\n[[Category:Ethers]]\n[[Category:Experimental cancer drugs]]\n[[Category:Non-receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitors]]\n[[Category:Aminopyrimidines]]\n\n{{antineoplastic-drug-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| IUPAC_name = (16''E'')-11-[2-(1-Pyrrolidinyl)ethoxy]-14,19-dioxa-5,7,26-triazatetracyclo[19.3.1.1<sup>2,6</sup>.1<sup>8,12</sup>]heptacosa-1(25),2(26),3,5,8,10,12(27),16,21,23-decaene\n| image = Pacritinib skeletal.svg\n| width = 230\n| alt = \n| caption =\n\n<!-- Clinical data -->\n| tradename = \n| Drugs.com = \n| MedlinePlus = \n| pregnancy_AU = <!-- A / B1 / B2 / B3 / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_US      = <!-- A / B / C / D / X -->\n| pregnancy_category= \n| legal_AU = <!-- S2, S3, S4, S5, S6, S7, S8, S9 or Unscheduled-->\n| legal_CA = <!-- OTC, Rx-only, Schedule I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII -->\n| legal_UK = <!-- GSL, P, POM, CD, CD Lic, CD POM, CD No Reg POM, CD (Benz) POM, CD (Anab) POM or CD Inv POM -->\n| legal_US = <!-- OTC / Rx-only / Schedule I, II, III, IV, V -->\n| legal_status = Investigational\n| routes_of_administration = Oral\n\n<!-- Pharmacokinetic data -->\n| bioavailability = \n| protein_bound = \n| metabolism = \n| elimination_half-life = \n| excretion =\n\n<!-- Identifiers -->\n| CAS_number = 937272-79-2\n| ATCvet = \n| ATC_prefix = None\n| ATC_suffix = \n| PubChem = 46216796\n| DrugBank = \n| KEGG = D11768\n| ChemSpiderID = 28518965 \n| ChEMBL = 2035187\n| synonyms = SB1518\n\n<!-- Chemical data -->\n| C=28 | H=32 | N=4 | O